        "special_abilities": [
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "An exhaust ooze is composed of transparent gas. While in an atmosphere, it can use Stealth to hide as part of a move action without the need for cover or concealment, and it takes no penalty to Stealth while moving at greater than half speed. As a standard action, the ooze can blend in with its environment, gaining a +10 bonus to Stealth until the beginning of its next turn.",
                "name": "Blend with Atmosphere",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "An exhaust ooze can batter its prey with a torrent of foul gas. A creature struck by this attack is exposed to the ooze\u2019s noxious fumes as if they had entered an area containing the poison. This attack is difficult to see\u2014although the target is automatically aware of it, other observers must succeed at a DC 25 Perception check to also be aware of it. Anyone aware of the attack is also aware of the ooze\u2019s presence and can sense from which direction the attack came, but is not aware of the ooze\u2019s location without a successful Perception check; they gain a +5 bonus to this check.",
                "name": "Noxious Torrent",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "An exhaust ooze can seep into the smallest of openings. The environmental protections of armor and space suits do not protect against the suffocating effects of the ooze\u2019s engulf ability unless the environmental protections come from an item of higher level than the ooze.",
                "name": "Suffocating Presence",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            }
        ],
